                     Vſe 3 Laſtly, let all ſuch as yet lye under the terrours of the Law, receive hence comfort; For the yoake ſhall bee deſtroyed, becauſe of the Oyle, Iſay. 10.27. You are come to Mount Sinai, which burnes with fire unto blackneſſe, darkneſſe and tempeſt;
                  Heb. 12.18. ſuch terrours as made Moſes himſelfe ſay, Expavefactus ſum ac tremebundus,

I quake exceedingly for feare: But here ſhall not be thy reſt, there is a Mount Sion thou art haſtening unto where thou ſhalt injoy the priviledges of the firſt borne, Gods purpoſe is not to leave thy ſoule in that diſtreſſed caſe.

